        a       owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1141  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In order to determine the subcellular localization of tomosyn-1, Fujita and colleagues divide rat cerebra in three fractions: cytosolic, detergent-soluble and detergent-insoluble fraction and perform immunoblotting for tomosyn-1 (after 1% Triton X-100 solubilization followed by 1h centrifugation at 100 000 x g). The protein is detected predominantly in the first two fractions (Fig. 6Ba).\nFurthermore, the authors fractionate rat synaptosomal fraction into cytosol, synaptic plasma membrane and synaptic vesicle fraction and detect highest enrichment of tomosyn-1 in the synaptic membrane fraction and also to some extent in the cytosolic fraction (Fig 6Bb). These results are in line with the observation of immunogold labelling of rat cerebellar molecular layer (Fig 6Da,c) and neuromuscular junction (Fig. 6Db,d).. Experimental description: Materials and Methods:\n\nPurification of Tomosyn from Rat Cerebral Cytosol\nAll purification procedures were performed at 0-4°C. GST-syntaxin-1a (1.2 nmol) or GST-Munc18 (1.2 nmol) were immobilized on glutathione Sepharose 4B beads (150 μl) to make an affinity column." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1141" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

